The paper discusses the security properties of gait-based pairing schemes for mobile devices, which involves analyzing the vulnerability of the system to attacks. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper also discusses the usability and human-computer interaction aspects of gait-based pairing, which could fall under the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computer and society (cs.CY). The paper also involves analyzing and processing data from sensors, which could fall under the categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
